Tesla has a big head start — what can the old car makers do?
Jurica Dujmovic lists competitors’ failed attempts to produce electric vehicles that can compete with Tesla TSLA, +8.21%, while Vitaliy Katsenelson has advice for older auto manufactures trying to catch up.

What might Google buy next?
Alphabet GOOG, -0.63%   GOOGL, -0.69%  — Google’s holding company — announced a deal on Nov. 1 to acquire Fitbit FIT, +0.14% for $2.1 billion in cash. Fitbit’s stock at the end of the day was up 66% from a week earlier (before the takeout rumors began). Jeff Reeves lists five other companies Alphabet may consider buying.

A Social Security decision
Catey Hill helps a 68-year-old man decide whether to wait another two years to begin receiving Social Security payments.

You can’t compete with these investing pros — but you can learn from them
You can’t beat the hedge-fund stars at what they do. So do what they don’t do. Gregory Zuckerman offers lessons for investors based on the successes and failures of Renaissance Technologies’ Jim Simons, the greatest money maker in modern financial history, according to Zuckerman.

A surgeon’s advice to fix the U.S. health care system
Marty Makary, a surgeon and the author of “The Price We Pay” describes the broken health care system and what can be done to fix it — some of which is already taking place.

